---
description: Next.js and React conventions for storefront and admin UI
globs: app/**/*.tsx,components/**/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---
- Use functional components with hooks only. No class components.
- Prefer Server Components by default; use `"use client"` only when interactivity is required (forms, cart, wishlist buttons).
- Fetch data in Server Components/route handlers, not in client-side useEffect, unless it's user-triggered.
- Use Tailwind utility classes only — no inline styles, no separate CSS files.
- Cart state: read/write via a single `lib/cart.ts` helper wrapping localStorage — don't scatter localStorage calls across components.
- Forms: validate with Zod before submitting to Supabase.
- Image components: always use `next/image`, never raw `<img>`.
